</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Upright Row Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended.</li>



<li>Lift dumbbells toward your chin, keeping your elbows higher than your wrists.</li>



<li>Lower weights back down and repeat. Avoid excessive momentum.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Hold the dumbbells shoulder-width apart, keeping a firm grip. Maintain an upright posture, retract your shoulder blades, and engage your core to prevent excessive stress on the shoulders and lower back.</li>



<li>Keep your elbows slightly higher than your hands throughout the movement, pulling the dumbbells toward your chin. Avoid excessive elevation, which can lead to shoulder strain.</li>



<li>Lift the weights smoothly with control, and lower them back down at a moderate pace. Avoid jerky movements to reduce the risk of injury and maximize muscle engagement in your upper back.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



