<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Incline-Dumbbell-Row">Incline Dumbbell Row</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/incline-dumbbell-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">incline dumbbell row</a> is one of the many popular <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/upper-back-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">upper back exercises</a> that intensely target the latissimus dorsi. This compound movement also utilizes the rhomboids, trapezius, biceps, and deltoids. Often used as a significant upper body strengthener, the incline dumbbell row also targets secondary muscles that aid stabilization.</p>



<p>The incline dumbbell row builds strength in the back and arms and helps improve posture. The exercise targets the core and contributes to better posture and overall <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10470156/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">better health</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="03271201-Dumbbell-Incline-Row_Back-FIX2_" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1004775158?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Incline Dumbbell Row Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin by setting a bench at a 45-degree angle. Lean forward on the bench, pressing your chest and abdomen into it. Straddle the bench with your knees soft and the balls of your feet firmly planted on the ground.</li>



<li>Grasping the handle of a dumbbell in each hand, inhale and extend your arms straight toward the floor. Palms should be facing toward yourself.</li>



<li>On an exhale, squeeze your shoulder blades together while pulling the dumbbells toward your chest. Elbows should raise toward the ceiling while the upper arms parallel to the floor.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale while slowly lowering the dumbbells back to the floor.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure that your shoulder blades stay retracted as your arms extend.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Avoid yanking the dumbbells. Instead, try to keep the motion smooth and fluid.&nbsp;</li>



<li>The bench’s position allows for more precise targeting of the back muscles. Try not to relax your entire body while being supported by the bench!</li>



<li><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/lower-back-stretches">Lower back stretches</a> can be a helpful addition to your workout program if you notice stiffness after a lifting session.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



