<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Reverse-Fly">Dumbbell Reverse Fly</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-reverse-fly" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell reverse fly</a> is an excellent compound movement for the upper body and can be modified for all populations. Aside from improving posture, it also aids in strengthening the muscles of the shoulders and upper back. If there are any noted asymmetries in the shoulder, this exercise can help provide balance and stability when done correctly.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The dumbbell reverse fly is a targeted exercise that works the posterior deltoids, rhomboids, teres minor, and trapezius. When these muscles are strengthened appropriately in a well-rounded fitness program, decreases in <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5721192/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">lower back pain</a> can be noted.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
